Author:
Vol / Page:  1100
Edition:
Quote:  <i>huia</i> also <i>huia bird n -s</i> [Maori <i>huia</i>] : a bird  (<i>Neomorpha acutirostris</i> or <i>Heteralocha acutirostris</i>) related to the starlings, confined to a small region in the mountains of New Zealand, and having black white-tipped tail feathers prized by Maori chiefs and worn as insignia of rank
